item.p:
This is a tranſlation or metraphraſe of that old La-Latin Diſtich;
Si Sol ſplendeſcat Maria purificante,
Major erit glacies poſt feſtum quam fuit ante. Now though I think all obſervations about particular days ſuperſtitious and frivolous, yet becauſe probably if the weather be fair for ſome days about this time of the year, it may betoken froſt, I have put this down as it was delivered me.

list.item:
                  i. e. In the time of affliction, a vow; in the time of proſperity an inundation: or a greater increaſe of wickednes.




The Devil was ſick, the Devil a monk would be;

The Devil was well, the Devil a monk was he.
